  "prompt": "The guy I'm seeing wants to have sex all the time. Does he respect me?",
  "response": "It's important to consider the context and dynamics of your relationship when evaluating whether someone respects you. Here are some key points to reflect on:\n\n1. **Communication**: Does he listen to your feelings, needs, and boundaries? Open and honest communication is a sign of respect. If he\u2019s willing to have conversations about your comfort levels and doesn\u2019t pressure you, that\u2019s a positive indicator.\n\n2. **Mutual Consent**: Does he prioritize your consent and ensure you\u2019re comfortable with any sexual activity? A respectful partner will always seek clear and enthusiastic consent and will respect your decisions without guilt or pressure.\n\n3. **Balance in the Relationship**: Does the relationship feel balanced, or does it seem primarily focused on sex? A healthy relationship involves emotional connection, shared interests, and mutual support, not just physical intimacy.\n\n4. **Your Feelings**: How do you feel in the relationship? Do you feel valued, heard, and respected as a person, or does it seem like your worth is tied to physical intimacy?\n\n5. **Boundaries**: Does he respect your boundaries, even if they differ from his desires? A respectful partner will honor your limits without trying to push or manipulate you.\n\nIf you\u2019re feeling uncomfortable, pressured, or like your needs aren\u2019t being considered, it\u2019s important to address this with him. A healthy relationship is built on mutual respect, trust, and understanding. If he dismisses your concerns or doesn\u2019t change his behavior, it could be a sign that he\u2019s not prioritizing your well-being. Trust your instincts and prioritize your own comfort and happiness.",
